<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08135</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING REPUBLIC ACT NO. 9136, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE "ELECTRIC POWER INDUSTRY REFORM ACT OF 2001" OR EPIRA, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to provide for the determination of the beneficiaries of the lifeline rate - the low-income or the marginalized end-users, to ensure that the Lifeline Rate subsidy will truly reach its intended beneficiaries.

Amends EPIRA to provide for a socialized pricing mechanism as follows:

100% discount – electricity consumption not exceeding 20 kwh;
  50% discount – electricity consumption not exceeding 50 kwh;
  35% discount – electricity consumption not exceeding 70 kwh;
 20% discount – electricity consumption not exceeding 100 kwh.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>UYBARRETA, CARLOS ROMAN</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-23</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Referred to Stakeholders on 2018-09-12</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ENERGY ON 2018-08-29</td></tr></table>